%N A272487 Decimal expansion of the edge length of a regular heptagon with unit circumradius.
%C A272487 The edge length e(m) of a regular m-gon is e(m) = 2*sin(Pi/m). In this case, m = 7, and the constant, a = e(7), is the smallest m for which e(m) is not constructible using a compass and a straightedge (see A004169). With an odd m, in fact, e(m) would be constructible only if m were a Fermat prime (A019434).
